      "statement": "It's rush hour at \"The Drooling Stein\", the goblins' favorite tavern. A long queue has formed in front of the counter. \nThe bartender, a tired old troll, can only serve one goblin per minute.\n\nHowever, goblins are known for their impatience. \nEach goblin in the queue has a [[patience]] level represented by a number of minutes. \nIf a goblin has to wait longer than their [[patience]] level, they leave the queue furiously and consume nothing.\n\nKnowing that the service starts at minute {{0}}, determine how many goblins will successfully get their beer before losing their [[patience]].\n\n<<Specific Rules>>\n- The goblin at the front of the queue is served instantly if his [[patience]] hasn't run out.\n- Serving a goblin takes exactly {{1}} minute (which advances the global time by {{1}}).\n- Goblins who lose [[patience]] leave the queue, which takes {{0}} minutes for the bartender.\n- The order of the queue does not change (no cutting in line).",
